Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT47) ATLANTA -- Oct. 19, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-21, 10-19 --
The New York Mets meet Kenny Rogers on the mound in the eleventh
inning of Game 6 of the National League Championship Series against
the Atlanta Braves on Tuesday night. The Braves won the game, 10-9,
and the best-of-seven series, 4-2. They will meet the New York
Yankees in the World Series. (G. Paul Burnett/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT46) ATLANTA -- Oct. 19, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-20, 10-19 --
Andruw Jones of the Atlanta Braves raises his hand in victory after
taking ball 4 from pitcher Kenny Rogers of the New York Mets with
the bases loaded in the eleventh inning of Game 6 of the National
League Championship Series on Tuesday night. The walk pushed home a
run and the Braves won the game, 10-9, and the best-of-seven
series, 4-2. They will meet the New York Yankees in the World
Series. (Renee Hannans/Atlanta Journal-Constitution Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT45) ATLANTA -- Oct. 19, 1999 -- BBN-METS-BRAVES-19, 10-19 --
