Benny Agbayani of the New York Mets scores past Greg Myers of the
Atlanta Braves in the tenth inning of Game 6 of the National League
Championship Series on Tuesday night. The run, delivered on a
sacrifice pop fly by Todd Pratt, briefly put the Mets up 9-8; the
Braves finished the game in the eleventh, 10-9, to win the series,
4-2. They will meet the New York Yankees in the World Series.
(Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
