showdown, President Clinton and the Republican Congress are
fighting over how much money the federal government should spend to
hire teachers and cops. They are also battling over how much money
the United States should pay to support the Middle East peace plan.
But their bitter standoff is about more than those issues or the
taxpayer dollars they represent. It is about seeking political
advantage. By Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
