overhaul and a soft money ban, lawmakers, including Democrats who
support McCain-Feingold, are increasing the number of pockets they
have for campaign donations. Some are launching leadership
political action committees at the state level which can take in
unrestricted, soft money contributions. By Don Van Natta.
</P>
