<P>
   WOM-GUTHRIE (New York) _ Janet Guthrie said that she harbors no
malice. Even 22 years ago, while a target of endless ``woman
driver'' jokes as the first female to drive in the Indianapolis
500, she was able to shrug off the sexist ridicule, the gratuitous
barbs. By Barbara Huebner. 1,200 words.
