<P>
   INDONESIA-POLITICS (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ In the first
democratic transfer of power in its history, Indonesia inaugurated
a new president Wednesday, Abdurrahman Wahid, a respected Moslem
leader whose message is tolerance, inclusion and self respect. The
vote for Wahid, 59, in an electoral assembly was a surprise. As
expected, there was violence on the streets of Jakarta as street
thugs joined disappointed supporters of the opposition leader who
had been expected to win the presidency, Megawati Sukarnoputri. By
Seth Mydans.
