recommend to FCC that Southwestern Bell be allowed into the
long-distance markets in Texas. This is a major goal for
Southwestern Bell. (Hight, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   UPS-IPO _ United Parcel Service set a target range of $36-$42 a
share for its upcoming IPO, in which it will sell stock publicly
for the first time. A midrange price of $39 would make the IPO
worth $4.2 billion, among the biggest ever. Also Wednesday, the
Teamsters announced that UPS had created 2,000 full-time jobs under
terms of the 1997 strike settlement. In the first two years of the
deal UPS had refused, citing a reduction on package volume.
(Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
