<P>
   INTERNET-PRIVACY _ WASHINGTON _ Americans are becoming
increasingly concerned about the need to protect their children
from sexually explicit material on the Internet, a new research
report into online privavcy and freedom of speech issues sponsored
by Kettering Foundation shows. Their concerns, however, do not
translate into support for having the government outlaw or censor
what's out there. (Glass, Cox News Service). 22.
</P>
<P>
   PEST-CONTROL _ WASHINGTON _ Plant pathologists at the U.S.
Department of Agriculture's Horticultural Research Laboratory at
Fort Pierce, Fla., have found that clear plastic laid over soil
before vegetable crops are planted creates enough heat to kill weed
seeds and diseases. Farmers now use methyl bromide, a
soon-to-be-banned ozone destroyer, for this purpose. (Nesmith, Cox
News Service). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
