   ELDERLY-GAYS (Fort Lauderdale, Fla.) _ As the first openly gay
generation grows grayer and contemplates retirement, developers are
planning retirement communities and assisted-care housing that
would allow aging gays to grow old surrounded by other gays. In
Fort Lauderdale, Boston, Los Angeles, San Francisco, Atlanta and
other cities, these developers are promising a haven for those who
will become old and infirm, many of them without the support of
children or other family members. ``When you're old, the last thing
that you want to do is to have to hide,'' a Fort Lauderdale
businessman said. By Rick Bragg. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``a'' news file.) 1,800 words.
