   HOLBROOKE-LOBBY (Washington) _ Since his confirmation as chief
delegate to the United Nations, Richard Holbrooke has turned
himself from high-flying diplomat to part-time lobbyist. He was
campaigning again Wednesday, and by midafternoon, the tally was 6
formal appointments, 14 chance encounters and more meetings to go,
all in the cause of rescuing the United States' standing at the
United Nations. By Jane Perlez. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``w'' news file.)
