   FRANCE-PAPON (Paris) _ With only hours to go before he was to
spend his first night in jail, Maurice Papon, the 89-year-old
career civil servant convicted last year of complicity in Nazi war
crimes, says he will flee the country rather than surrender. By
Suzanne Daley. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
