<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NCR-EARNINGS21-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   NCR registers solid third-quarter report
</P>
<P>
   By Laura A. Bischoff
</P>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ NCR Corp. more than doubled its third-quarter
earnings to $53 million, or 53 cents per share, easily exceeding
analysts' estimates, company officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Boosting the earnings were a number of real estate sales and
one-time gains. Without those special items, earnings from
operating income was 44 cents per share _ still 3 cents ahead of
the analysts consensus estimate of 41 cents per share.
</P>
<P>
   NCR saw strong growth in its retail store automation and
automatic teller machine businesses, said NCR Chairman and Chief
Executive Lars Nyberg.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are seeing market confirmation that our strategy and
emphasis on data warehousing is the right one, although we continue
to face challenges for our data warehousing solutions in the
financial industry,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   He noted that the data warehouses _ huge computers that track
vast amounts of information _ are selling well in the airline,
retail and telecommunications industries.
</P>
<P>
   Overall sales were down 2 percent _ a decline NCR attributes to
it getting out of the computer hardware commodity market.
Third-quarter sales this year were $1.53 billon compared with $1.55
billion for the same period last year. For the first nine months of
the year, sales were $4.435 billion compared with $4.438 for the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
   Sales of retail automation systems in the third quarter
increased 32 percent to $253 million, while ATM and related
services sales increased 10 percent to $280 million. Data
warehousing sales fell 4 percent to $180 million and customer
services maintenance fell 8 percent to $427 million.
</P>
<P>
   Chief Financial Officer David Bearman told Wall Street stock
analysts Wednesday that NCR's key businesses are healthy and data
warehousing is looking promising.
</P>
<P>
   He told analysts that NCR is expecting to sign up new data
warehousing customers in the fourth quarter and revenues will show
healthy increases over last year, but that retail store automation
and financial self service revenues may decline over last year's
numbers.
</P>
<P>
   NCR officials will hold another conference call on Tuesday to
discuss the company's long-term strategies.
</P>
<P>
   NCR's stock (NYSE:NCR) closed on Wednesday at 28, up 1 1/4 on a
volume of 1,396,000.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
