<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-MATCHUP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHIEFS AT RAVENS 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; THURSDAY NIGHT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City (3-2) at Baltimore (2-3)
</P>
<P>
   The Ravens are always in games, making them close, hanging
around. Their last four contests have been decided by seven points
or less. Normally, your typical Kansas City team, which won in Week
5 against New England and had a bye last week, would lose a game
they were expected to win after winning a game they were expected
to lose. This Chiefs team has a different feel and they also have
the better offense.
</P>
<P>
   Chiefs, 24-20
</P>
