<SLUG> BC-RAC-RACENOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLASSIC OLYMPIO DOESN'T DISAPPOINT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRANK C. GIRARDOT  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA, Calif. _ Back after breaking her maiden, Classic
Olympio showed Wednesday why she was the favorite in Wednesday's
$75,000 Anoakia Stakes at Santa Anita.
</P>
<P>
   Despite a late run from second choice She's Classy, Classic
Olympio stormed to her second win and paid $3.20, $2.20 and $2.20.
</P>
<P>
   Trained by Ron McAnally, Classic Olympio covered the 6 furlongs
in 1:09.70 with Alex Solis in the saddle.
</P>
<P>
   She's Classy, ridden by Victor Espinoza, paid $2.60 and $2.60.
Third was Bold Feat, with Corey Black up. Bold Feat paid $2.80.
</P>
<P>
   __ Big field expected: Saturday's $250,000 Grade II Oak Tree
Derby could draw a large field of 3-year-olds. Part of the reason
is the cancellation of last weekend's Ascot Handicap at Bay Meadows
in Northern California. The race was taken off the card when safety
concerns forced officials to close the Bay Meadows turf course.
</P>
<P>
   The race has not been rescheduled, so several Northern
California trainers are looking for a race that fits their
3-year-olds.
</P>
<P>
   One of those trainers is Thomas R. Bell, who might run Good
Fellow Robin in the 1[-mile race. In his last local run, Good
Fellow Robin finished fourth in the Pomona Derby.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the Pomona Derby, he really didn't handle the (Fairplex)
bullring,'' Bell said. ``He seemed a bit confused about the
dimensions of everything there.''
</P>
<P>
   Other probables for the Oak Tree Derby include Eagleton,
Fighting Falcon, Outstanding Hero, Prime Timber, Red Sea,
Rhapsodist, Super Quercus and Zanetti.
</P>
<P>
   __ Uncoupled: Look for two Bob Baffert-trained horses in
Friday's Sunny Slope Stakes. Just don't expect them to run as an
entry. Baffert will run Cameron Pass with Gary Stevens and Magical
Dragon with David Flores as an uncoupled entry in the $75,000
6-furlong test for 2-year-olds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
